                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A4e/657: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Delegation</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-11-24T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 24, 1926—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>279. Department’s telegram No. 237, October 20, 3 p.m.<note n="30"
                        xml:id="d648fn30">Not printed.</note> What is present status of
                    Russo-Asiatic Bank matter and question of reallocation of customs funds among
                    banks in China?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
